data.description: Welcome to this executive brick home, perfectly situated on a corner lot in the Dunwoody section of the Shadowmoss neighborhood in West Ashley.  Once inside, you will be greeted by beautiful hardwood floors and a grand two-story foyer.  Immediately to the left is a formal office with custom designed sliding barn-doors. This space could also be used as a study or sitting room.  To the right is the formal dining room graced by a large window and plenty of room for a china cabinet and dining room table.  The main living room is bright and sunny, and the large windows allow natural light to flow through with beautiful plantation shutters.  A designer marble inlay in the hardwood floor highlights the wood burning fireplace.  The large eat-in kitchen is perfect for entertainingas it opens directly into the living room.  The kitchen has unique features such as a pressed-tin backsplash, Silestone countertops, and beautiful stainless-steel appliances.  The screened porch has a ceiling fan and leads to the patio, a perfect spot for grilling.  The fenced in wrap around yard offers plenty of space for children and animals to securely play and gives those with a green thumb endless opportunities to be creative.  The backyard also has a spacious shed for a variety of storage needs.   In addition, the spacious attached two-car garage has a loft storage area. The owner's suite is conveniently located on the first floor and features a tray ceiling, ceiling fan, carpeting, and a decorative window.  The stylish owner's bathroom with a vaulted ceiling, dual sink vanity, private water closet, and a large shower that leads to a private outdoor shower that is surrounded by bamboo.  The owner's suite closet is impressive as it encompasses 1.5 stories, it provides a loft with stairs that access the second level.     Upstairs you will find three spacious bedrooms each with hardwood floors and ceiling fans.  At the top of the stairs, there is access to a large area for attic storage.  Two of the guest bedrooms share a full Jack-and-Jill style bathroom.  The large FROG (family room over the garage) has Berber carpet and could be perfect as a Man-Cave, office space, or second family room.  The home also features 2 HVAC systems that service both the 1st and 2nd floor zones.  The 1st floor unit is new.  There is a golf club, 18 hole semi-private golf course, and pool within the neighborhood.  Inquire about membership through the Shadowmoss Moss Golf Club.  This desirable community is located near hospitals, shopping, restaurants, retail, and more.  Downtown Charleston is just 20 minutes away, just a 30-minute drive in different directions is Folly Beach and Kiawah and Seabrook Islands, and Historic Summerville is a short 35-minute drive too.  It is a must see to fully appreciate all it has to offer.
